[CENTER][SIZE=6][B]🌙 RPGMood[/B][/SIZE][/CENTER]
[CENTER][I]Give your vanilla server a pulse — mobs that scale with danger, zones that react to where you are, and deaths that tell a story.[/I][/CENTER]

RPGMood layers atmosphere and a sense of place on top of unmodified vanilla survival. Hostile mobs grow stronger the further players wander from spawn, entering a new region shows a title and plays a sound, and dying gets a narrative death message instead of the flat vanilla one — all without touching loot tables, crafting, or PvP balance.

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]⚔ Mob Scaling[/B][/SIZE]

Hostile mobs gain levels based on [B]distance from spawn[/B], [B]biome[/B], [B]nearby vanilla structures[/B], and [B]how many players are nearby[/B] — shown live in the mob's name (Lv. 12 Zombie).

[LIST]
[*]Health, attack damage, armor, and movement speed all scale with level — health and damage share one even curve tuned to each mob's own real vanilla stats, so scaling feels consistent between mob types instead of a level-1 zombie and a level-1 Enderman ending up wildly mismatched
[*]Per-mob-type difficulty seeds (Zombie is easier than Wither Skeleton at the same distance)
[*]Biome and structure bonuses are fully configurable — make deserts scarier, or strongholds a real threat
[*][B]Aggro range scales with the same curve[/B] — weak early-game mobs notice you from a bit less far than vanilla, dangerous late-game mobs just as far or farther
[*][B]Night and thunderstorm bonuses[/B] stack extra difficulty on top of the existing distance/biome/structure/player scaling
[*][B]Radial spawn protection[/B] — hostile mobs no longer naturally spawn within a configurable radius of world spawn
[*]Structure-proximity checks are cached per region, so this stays cheap even with heavy mob spawning
[*][B]Bonus XP on kill[/B], proportional to the mob's level — difficulty isn't just punishment
[*][B]Server-wide announcement[/B] when a dangerously high-level mob spawns (configurable threshold and cooldown)
[*]Every scaled mob's level is exposed via PersistentDataContainer for other plugins (e.g. loot plugins) to hook into
[*]Fully tunable in config.yml: growth curve, max level cap, night/thunder bonuses, spawn-protection radius, and every bonus source
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]👹 Mob Affixes[/B][/SIZE]

Scaled mobs can roll [B]1–2 affixes[/B], odds increasing with level, each flagged by a subtle particle marker and a one-time action-bar warning (name tags stay off by default):

[LIST]
[*][B]Swift[/B] — noticeably faster, up to 40% at higher levels
[*][B]Wraith[/B] — turns invisible; the particle marker is your only tell
[*][B]Regenerating[/B] — heals over time mid-fight
[*][B]Bleeding[/B] — on-hit chance to inflict a stacking bleed DOT on you
[*][B]Poisonous[/B] — on-hit chance to poison you
[*][B]Chilling[/B] — on-hit chance to slow you
[/LIST]

Proc chances, durations, and bonus magnitudes are all tunable under mob_scaling.affixes in config.yml.

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]🗺 Zones[/B][/SIZE]

Crossing into a new zone shows a title/subtitle, plays a sound and particles, and drops a short flavor line in chat a moment later.

[LIST]
[*][B]Biome zones[/B] — trigger when you enter a configured biome
[*][B]WorldGuard zones[/B] — trigger when you step inside a named WorldGuard region (optional integration)
[*][B]Unclaimed areas[/B] aren't left blank — every corner of the map gets a procedurally-combined name (e.g. "Elden Meadows", "the ash-choked Sunlit Barrows") built by recombining a pool of biome-appropriate adjectives and nouns, giving hundreds of unique names per biome without repeating
[*][B]Zone titles are colored by local danger[/B] — the same 5-tier palette RPGLoot uses for item rarity (gray → yellow → purple → green → gold), based on the mob level at that location
[*][B]Optional sidebar scoreboard[/B] (/rpgmood toggle scoreboard) shows your current zone, local danger level, and session kill count; a temporary danger-colored BossBar also flashes on every zone change
[*][B]/rpgmood zones[/B] lists every zone you've discovered — biome, danger level, first-seen date — lets you mark favorites, and shows distance to your nearest known zone
[*][B]Per-zone music[/B] — an optional namespaced sound key (resource-pack friendly) plays once on entry
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]💀 Death Messages[/B][/SIZE]

Every death gets a narrative message instead of the vanilla one — composed, not just picked from a list:

[LIST]
[*]A core line reacts to [B]cause of death[/B], [B]biome[/B], and [B]killer type[/B] — including PvP kills, which correctly name the killing player
[*]Killer names get randomized synonyms (a Zombie might be called a "shambling snack" or "graveyard gremlin")
[*]An independent ~45% chance appends a closing flourish ("The night keeps its own score.")
[*]Location names get an independent descriptor prefix ("the storm-worn Elden Meadows")
[*]The same exact line won't fire twice in a row for the same player
[/LIST]

Every death is also saved to the player's persistent adventure journal.

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]🖥 GUI Menu[/B][/SIZE]

/rpgmood with no arguments (or /rpgmood menu explicitly) opens an inventory-based hub — every system below, in one place, no commands to memorize:

[LIST]
[*][B]Adventure Journal[/B], [B]Achievements[/B] (filterable by category), [B]Current Zone[/B] (open to every player, not just admins), [B]Leaderboard[/B], [B]Farming[/B], [B]My Animals[/B], and [B]Settings[/B] panels
[*]If [B]RPGLoot[/B] is installed, an extra panel shows your equipped rarities, active set, and lifetime loot stats
[*]Admins get an [B]Admin Config[/B] panel — steppers for spawn-protection radius, the mob-scaling curve, night/thunder bonuses, and the weather-effects toggle, writing straight to config.yml with no file editing required
[*]Every existing text command (/diary, /rpgmood leaderboard, /rpgmood-farm, etc.) still works exactly as before — the menu is an addition, not a replacement
[*]Tab-completion on /rpgmood, /diary, and /rpgmood-farm
[*]Custom join/quit messages (action-bar or chat, per player preference) with a distinct message and sound for a player's very first join
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]📖 Adventure Journal & Leaderboard[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*]/diary opens a written book listing the player's recent zone arrivals and deaths, timestamped and persisted across restarts
[*]/rpgmood leaderboard shows the top 10 players by deaths, zone changes, or highest-level mob killed
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]📈 Player Progression[/B][/SIZE]

/rpgmood level — a player progression level, separate from mob difficulty levels, shown right on the GUI menu's front page.

[LIST]
[*]Earned from scaled-mob kills and discovering new zones
[*]Every 5 levels raises your farm animal ownership cap by 1
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]🏆 Achievements[/B][/SIZE]

[B]31 achievements[/B] across exploration, combat, survival, and farming — /rpgmood achievements shows your progress grouped by category, unlocked ones announced in chat and logged to your journal.

Not just grindy counters — the roster leans into things players actually chase for bragging rights: [B]Godslayer[/B] (kill the Warden, Wither, Elder Guardian, [I]and[/I] Ender Dragon), [B]Untouchable[/B] (kill a level 20+ mob without ever taking damage from it), [B]Cartographer[/B] (discover every zone you've configured), [B]Noah's Ark[/B] (own one of every farm animal), and more. All persisted to achievements.yml, survive restarts.

If [B]RPGLoot[/B] is installed, 6 additional Loot achievements unlock — [B]Legendary Hunter[/B], [B]Relic Bearer[/B], and the ultimate flex, [B]Godslayer's Arsenal[/B] (collect all 4 of RPGLoot's boss-exclusive Artifacts). Zero setup required and zero effect if RPGLoot isn't installed.

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]🌾 Harvest Moon-Style Farming[/B][/SIZE]

A full farming, cooking, and animal-husbandry module (/rpgmood-farm), inspired by Harvest Moon NES/N64:

[LIST]
[*][B]Crop quality[/B] — every harvest scores Bronze/Silver/Gold based on soil fertility (per biome), nearby water, rain, and the zone's danger level
[*][B]Four seasons[/B] (Spring/Summer/Autumn/Winter, 30 MC days each) — each with its own growth multiplier and season-exclusive crops
[*][B]Cooking & recipes[/B] — discovered by experimenting with ingredients in a crafting table, grant temporary "Mood" buffs (bonus damage, regeneration, bonus XP)
[*][B]Animal husbandry, no shop involved[/B] — feed a wild cow/chicken/sheep/goat its normal vanilla breeding food and it's yours; pet, feed, milk, and shear claimed animals, and breeding automatically grows your herd under a shared owner. An affection system drives product quality, and neglect leads to sickness
[*][B]Fine-grained permissions[/B] — rpgmood.player.farming splits into .season/.crops/.recipes/.animal nodes if you want to restrict any single piece (all enabled by default)
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]🌦 Ambient Time & Weather Events[/B][/SIZE]

RPGMood keeps the world feeling alive around you, not just when something notable happens:

[LIST]
[*]Scheduled messages and sounds tied to time-of-day (dawn, midday, dusk, midnight) and weather transitions (rain/thunder start and stop)
[*][B]Ambient sounds[/B] — low-probability birdsong and eerie ambience play near each player, independent of the scripted time/weather messages
[*][B]Weather now has mechanical bite[/B] — brief Darkness pulses during thunderstorms and small wind nudges during rain under open sky, both checked against the world's live weather state
[*][B]Nether acid rain[/B] — a periodic hazard for the one dimension vanilla weather doesn't reach
[*]Chance-based flavor messages on breaking configured blocks
[*]All fully defined in triggers.yml and config.yml
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]🔌 Integrations & Developer API[/B][/SIZE]

All optional — RPGMood works standalone and detects these automatically at startup.

[LIST]
[*][B]PlaceholderAPI[/B] — %rpgmood_zone%, %rpgmood_area_danger% for scoreboards and tab list
[*][B]WorldGuard[/B] — enables region-based zones
[*][B]RPGLoot[/B] — soft, zero-dependency integration in both directions: RPGLoot raises drop rarity floors near dangerous RPGMood mobs, and RPGMood's achievements react to RPGLoot's rarities/artifacts/sets. Neither plugin requires the other.
[*][B]Public API for developers[/B] — PlayerZoneChangeEvent, MobScaleEvent, PlayerDeathMessageEvent, PlayerCropHarvestEvent let other plugins hook into RPGMood without a hard dependency
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]🛠 Admin Tools[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*]/rpgmood info shows your current zone and the mob difficulty level a Zombie, Skeleton, and Enderman would each get at your exact location — the fastest way to sanity-check your mob_scaling tuning without waiting for a real mob to spawn
[*]/rpgmood reload and /rpgmood toggle remain available for scripting and console use
[*]The in-game [B]Admin Config[/B] GUI panel (see GUI Menu above) covers the same tuning with steppers, no file editing required
[*]config.yml, zones.yml, triggers.yml, and farming.yml all [B]auto-merge new keys[/B] on startup or reload — updating RPGMood never silently wipes a config you've already customized
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B]📦 Installation[/B][/SIZE]

1. Drop rpgmood.jar into your /plugins folder
2. Restart the server
3. Done — config.yml, zones.yml, triggers.yml, and farming.yml generate automatically

[B]Requirements:[/B] Paper/Spigot 1.20.4+ · Java 21+ · No required dependencies

